-- Chevron Oil Pipeline Leak Contained in Salt Lake City After a Day, AP Says
-- Kari Lundgren
-- 2010-06-13T09:43:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/chevron-oil-pipeline-leak-contained-in-salt-lake-city-after-a-day-ap-says.html

          
          
             A damaged  Chevron Corp . pipeline
leaked as much as 500 barrels of oil into a Salt Lake City creek
on June 11 before being contained, the Associated Press
reported.  
 The underground pipeline broke at about 10 a.m. and city
officials were alerted early the next day, the newswire said.
The cause of the leak is unknown, AP reported, citing fire
department spokesman Scott Freitag and local Mayor  Ralph Becker .  
